observationText: The nf1bΔ 55 mutant allele was generated by application of modularly assembled zinc finger nucleases (ZFNs) targeting exon 17 of the nf1b gene in zebrafish.
Zebrafish homozygous for the nf1bΔ 55 mutation in combination with homozygous loss of nf1a exhibited larval lethality between 7 and 10 days post fertilization.
